The Windows networking workgroup or domain that the user is part of. In order for a new workgroup to fully take effect the user may need to log out and log back in.
提供代理配置值的 URL。
The port on the machine defined by "/system/proxy/socks_host" that you proxy through.
代理套接字的机器名。
The port on the machine defined by "/system/proxy/ftp_host" that you proxy through.
代理 FTP 的机器名。

local_schema.short_desc: 安全 HTTP 代理端口
local_schema.longdesc: The port on the machine defined by "/system/proxy/secure_host" that you proxy through.

local_schema.short_desc: 安全 HTTP 代理主机名
local_schema.longdesc: 代理安全 HTTP 的机器名。
Select the proxy configuration mode. Supported values are "none", "manual", "auto".

This key contains a list of hosts which are connected to directly, rather than via the proxy (if it is active). The values can be hostnames, domains (using an initial wildcard like *.foo.com), IP host addresses (both IPv4 and IPv6) and network addresses with a netmask (something like 192.168.0.0/24).
用于 HTTP 代理认证的密码。
用于 HTTP 代理认证的用户名。

If true, then connections to the proxy server require authentication. The username/password combo is defined by "/system/http_proxy/authentication_user" and "/system/http_proxy/authentication_password".
The port on the machine defined by "/system/http_proxy/host" that you proxy through.
代理 HTTP 的机器名。
Enables the proxy settings when accessing HTTP over the Internet.

local_schema.short_desc: DNS-SD 服务应查阅的额外域
local_schema.longdesc: Comma separated list of DNS-SD domains that should be visible in the "network:///" location.

local_schema.short_desc: 如何显示本地 DNS-SD 服务
local_schema.longdesc: 可供选择的值有“merged”、“separate”和“disabled”。

GStreamer can put visualization plugins in a pipeline to transform audio stream in video frames. Default is goom but more visualization plugins will be ported soon. The visualization plugin can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.
GStreamer can record video from any number of input elements. Some possible choices are v4lsrc and videotestsrc. The video source can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.
Describes the selected input element.
GStreamer can record audio using any number of input elements. Some possible choices are osssrc, esdsrc and alsasrc. The audio source can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.

GStreamer can play video using any number of output elements. Some possible choices are xvimagesink, ximagesink, sdlvideosink and aasink. The videosink can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.

local_schema.short_desc: description for GStreamer audiosink for Audio/Video Conferencing
local_schema.longdesc: Describes the selected output element for Audio/Video Conferencing.
GStreamer can play audio using any number of output elements. Some possible choices are osssink, esdsink and alsasink. The audiosink can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.

local_schema.short_desc: description for GStreamer audiosink for Music and Movies
local_schema.longdesc: Describes the selected output element for Music and Movies.

local_schema.short_desc: GStreamer audiosink for Music and Movies
local_schema.longdesc: GStreamer can play audio using any number of output elements. Some possible choices are osssink, esdsink and alsasink. The audiosink can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.
Describes the selected output element.
GStreamer can play audio using any number of output elements. Some possible choices are osssink, esdsink and alsasink. The audiosink can be a partial pipeline instead of just one element.
If true, scrolling one direction through all workspaces is possible.
How often to check for new weather information.
The name of the weather source to get weather information from.
If true, use metric units when showing weather.
The list of weather locations to check.

local_schema.short_desc: Dismiss a stopped timer when clicked
local_schema.longdesc: If false, finished timers will reset instead of dismiss.
The default time (in secs) for any new timers.
If true, all new timers will automatically start.
If true, timers will disappear when they time out.
The currently selected item in the session manager menu.
The number of most recent documents to show.
If true, will try to show the most recent document on the dock.
List of NPR stations to display.
The GMail username to check.
How often (in mins) to check for new mail.

local_schema.short_desc: Show a notify for unread mail
local_schema.longdesc: If true, shows a notify message for new unread mail.

local_schema.short_desc: Show indicator dot for unread mail
local_schema.longdesc: If true, when there is new unread mail Docky will show the indicator dot.
The last time Docky checked GMail for messages.
List of custom GMail labels to check in addition to the inbox.
How much to shift the color of the urgent indicator. The value can be from -180 to 180.
The name of the current Docky theme.

local_schema.short_desc: Urgent indicator glow animation time (in seconds)
local_schema.longdesc: How long the urgent indicator glow animation is (in seconds), 0 to disable, or -1 for infinite.

local_schema.short_desc: Redirect helper output to Docky's output
local_schema.longdesc: If true, output from the helpers will be redirected to show in Docky's output.

local_schema.short_desc: Show hover text labels for launchers
local_schema.longdesc: If false, Docky will not show hover texts for launchers (but still show for plugins).

local_schema.short_desc: Show windows from only current desktop
local_schema.longdesc: If true, Docky will only show windows on the currently active desktop.
If the 'Pin to Dock' option should show in the menu of items, allowing you to add it permanently to the dock.

local_schema.short_desc: Show Settings in Docky item menu
local_schema.longdesc: If true, the Docky item popup menu shows the Settings option.

local_schema.short_desc: Show Quit in Docky item menu
local_schema.longdesc: If true, the Docky item popup menu shows the Quit option.
If true, shows the Docky item on the dock managing windows.
Set the color of the Docky icon. 0 means use the GTK+ theme color.
The text to show when hovering the Docky item.
The command to execute when left-clicking the Docky item or "" for default behavior (which opens the configuration dialog).
If true, this is the first time Docky has run. Internal use only - Do not change!
The dock's zoom size (if enabled), as a percent.
If true, the dock will zoom when hovered.
If true, any windows without launchers will show on this dock. Exactly 1 dock must have this set to true.
If true, the dock is drawn as a 3d dock.

local_schema.short_desc: Sorts the items on the dock
local_schema.longdesc: Used to sort the items on the dock.
The dock's position on the screen. Possible values are: Bottom, Top, Left, Right
A list of plugins that are active on this dock.

local_schema.short_desc: If the dock is a panel
local_schema.longdesc: If true, the dock is in panel mode and will extend to fill the entire screen edge.

local_schema.short_desc: Which monitor the dock is on
local_schema.longdesc: This is the monitor the dock exists on.
This is the list of all the launchers on this dock.

local_schema.short_desc: Indicate when items have more than one window
local_schema.longdesc: If true, items with more than one window have two indicator dots instead of just one dot.
The size of icons on the dock.
The number of extra pixels to pad the hover area on the top of the dock.
If fading when hiding, this is the opacity the dock fades to. 1 is solid, 0 is invisible.
If true, when the dock hides it will fade away instead of sliding off screen.
The dock's hide mode. Possible values are: None, Autohide, Intellihide, UniversalIntellihide
If false, prevents dropping items onto the dock to add them to the dock.
If true, locks all items on all docks so they can't be dragged.

local_schema.short_desc: How long to wait (ms) to update after a window switch
local_schema.longdesc: This is the time (in milliseconds) to wait to determine if a window switch causes a (un)hide.

local_schema.short_desc: How long to wait (ms) before unhiding
local_schema.longdesc: This is the time (in milliseconds) to wait before unhiding a hidden dock when the cursor moves over it.
If true, Docky will check for compositing and warn if it is not available.
This lists all the currently active (displayed) docks, by name.
This is the command to execute when left clicking on the CPU docklet item.
If true, shows time in 24-hr format.
If true, show the digital clock otherwise show the analog clock.
If true, the date should show on the digital clock.
The theme for the analog clock.
If true, tracks the mouse selection clipboard. If false, tracks the secondary clipboard.
How often to poll (in ms) for new clipboard data.
How many recent clipboard selections to show.
Toggle whether guake will hide when it loses focus.
Toggle main guake window fullscreen.
Paste the clipboard content.
Copy the clipboard content.
Decrease the terminal transparency.
Increase the terminal transparency.
Decrease the screen height.
Increase the screen height.
Decrease the font size of the terminals.
Additional shortcut for zooming in.
Increase the font size of the terminals.
Shows a dialog to rename the current tab.
Switch to the tenth tab.
Switch to the ninth tab.
Switch to the eighth tab.
Switch to the seventh tab.
Switch to the sixth tab.
Switch to the fifth tab.
Switch to the fourth tab.
Switch to the third tab.
Switch to the second tab.
Switch to the first tab.
Shows the next tab.
Shows the previous tab.
Move the current tab to the right
Move the current tab to the left

local_schema.short_desc: Search current selected text on the web
local_schema.longdesc: Accelerator to active function that search on the web the current selected text on the terminal.
Accelerator to active function that closes the current selected tab.
Calls the function to add a new tab in guake window.
Quit Guake.
Reset terminal
Global keybinding to allow user call guake from each place after it's opened without clicks.
Controls the shape of the cursor in the terminals. 0: Block, 1: I-Beam, 2: Underline

local_schema.short_desc: Cursor blink mode of the terminal
local_schema.longdesc: Controls the blink mode of the cursor in the terminals. 0: Follow GTK+ setting, 1: Blink on, 2: Blink off
Alpha that will be applied to the terminal background.
Background image that will be used in terminal.
Background color that will be used in terminal.

local_schema.short_desc: Allow displaying bold font in Guake terminal
local_schema.longdesc: When allow_bold is disabled, any text in Guake terminal intended to print as bold text will be instead rendered as normal text.
Color scheme name that will be used in terminal.
Color scheme that will be used in terminal.
Font color that will be used in terminal.
Font face and size that will be used in terminal.

local_schema.short_desc: Path to the default custom command json file.
local_schema.longdesc: Path to the default custom command json file. If is blank or the json file is not in a proper format the terminal context menu will be built without custom commands. If the file is a valid json with recognized structure theterminak context menu will be buit with the commands read inside.

local_schema.short_desc: Give focus to guake if tab is opened (OBSOLETE).
local_schema.longdesc: If the guake window is out of focus but open, enabling this will give it back the focus instead of closing the window.

local_schema.short_desc: If the tabs bar must be visible in fullscreen
local_schema.longdesc: Set it as false to enjoy guake's fullscreen.

local_schema.short_desc: If guake must show a control to make resizing more handful
local_schema.longdesc: When true, guake shows a resizer on its bottom to allow user resize guake.

local_schema.short_desc: Characters that are considered "part of a word"
local_schema.longdesc: When selecting text by word, sequences of these characters are considered single words. Ranges can be given as "A-Z". Literal hyphen (not expressing a range) should be the first character given.
Defines the behavior of delete key.
Defines the behavior of backscape key.

local_schema.short_desc: Use terminal titles for tab naming
local_schema.longdesc: Any terminal program can set the terminal's title via special escape sequences. Some shells (e.g. bash) display user's prompt there (though you can adjust that to any arbitrary text in bashrc or similar) and update it automatically as the prompt changes. So you can have easy automatically updating meaningful tab titles with this option turned on.

local_schema.short_desc: Use palette font and backgrount colors
local_schema.longdesc: If true, the terminal font and background colors will use the value defined in the palette. If false, it will use the value defined by the user.
If true, Guake will use the GNOME monospace default font.
If true and a key is pressed, the terminal is scrolled to the bottom.
If true, whenever there is new output in the terminal, it will scroll to the bottom.
The number of scrollback lines to save in history.
When true, scrollbar is visible.
Place Guake at: 0: top, 1: bottom
Place Guake at: 0: center, 1: left, 2: right
Percent of the screen that will be used by guake terminal vertically.
Percent of the screen that will be used by guake terminal horizontally.
Percent of the screen that will be used by guake terminal horizontally.
If true, the terminal will flash on a bell character.
If true, the system alert sound will be played on a bell character.
When true, the program will start in fullscreen mode.

local_schema.short_desc: Startup script to execute when guake starts
local_schema.longdesc: This property allows you to execute a startup bash script each time guake starts. You can configure your initial tab settings within this script. Please see the command line argument of guake ('guake --help') for complete help.

local_schema.short_desc: Quick open the file in the current terminal.
local_schema.longdesc: If this property is set as true, guake will use the current terminal to execute the Quick open feature. Use if you want to inherit your terminal environment in your text editor

local_schema.short_desc: Command line pattern to start a editor.
local_schema.longdesc: This property gives the command line to execute when doing a Quick Open. You can enter the following python string pattern in it: '%(file_path)s' will be replaced with the full path to the captured filename, '%(line_number)s' will be replaced by the line number if found (set to the empty string otherwise).
If this property is set as true, guake will open a text editor when the user does a Ctrl+Click on a filename printed in the terminal.
When true, the tab bar is visible.

local_schema.short_desc: Determine if guake hides on lose focus.
local_schema.longdesc: If this property is set as true, guake will be hidden when the main window lose the focus (when Alt+Tab be pressed for example).
Makes tab bar on top of the Guake window. Per default, tabs appears bellow the terminal. Setting this to True will move the tab on top of the terminal. Requires a restart.
Makes guake window be on top of all other windows in the desktop.
0: Never 1: If process is running 2: Always. Also prompts on quit.
Ask for confirmation when quitting Guake.
When true, popup notifications will be shown when Guake starts.
When true tray is visible.
If true, the commands in terminal will be executed in a login shell.
Path to the default shell. Set to empty to use default user shell. If invalid path is set here, guake will fallback to user shell.

Display to appear on if the mouse_display option is not set. If this is set to an invalid value (as in the case of removing a screen from a system), the invalid value is automatically updated to the current primary screen.
Appear on the mouse display. This overrides any setting in display_n.
When debug mode is enabled, logs are printed in the standard output where Guake as been launched
